s no way to prevent the corruption that always follows the concentration of power (Jacobin? Why not just call yourself Murderous Gang of Thugs). They foolishly believe that good people would run a just government, so they are fine with strong centralized government and laws that protect people from poor decisions. Like children running to their mother, they come to the conclusion that the real problem is that the wrong people are running the government.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div></li><li class="comment byuser odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent " id="comment-7758358" data-sort-time="1555447188"><div id="div-comment-7758358" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>DWB</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/04/16/are-socialists-more-like-libertarians-than-wed-like-to-admit/#comment-7758358">April.16.2019 at 4:39 pm </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>Have you ever considered that you are not a libertarian, but just a chick of low morals who loves her some baby killin&#8217;??????</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div><ol class="children"><li class="comment byuser even depth-2 parent " id="comment-7758471" data-sort-time="1555450732"><div id="div-comment-7758471" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>mad.casual</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/04/16/are-socialists-more-like-libertarians-than-wed-like-to-admit/#comment-7758471">April.16.2019 at 5:38 pm </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p><i>who loves her some baby killin’??????</i></p><p>In the past she&#8217;s been on board with murdering toddlers too.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div><ol class="children"><li class="comment byuser odd alt depth-3" id="comment-7758570" data-sort-time="1555457968"><div id="div-comment-7758570" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetada